{"key":"processedPost-13146007","value":{"id":13146007,"first":13145561,"last":13149867,"when":1283610131,"utime":"09/04/10 05:22 PM","content":"Those cheap hepa filters with paper inserts will let lots of crap get through.&nbsp; They also have very high flow rates, and stir up dust.&nbsp; I run one of those in the winter when we have our wood stove running.&nbsp; It tends to help keep the dust from ash down in the house.&nbsp; Still, mrs rabbit has to dust the furniture at least once a week or we can write our name in the dust.&nbsp; Those things help clean the air in a large room, but are no replacement for a flow hood.<br /><br />If you run one to reduce contaminant load in your room, be sure to shut it off when you use your glovebox, which works on the principle of still air, not sterile air.<br />RR","title":"Re: \"true hepa filter\"","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}